<subSubSection lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="236" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,294,2017]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,303,745,771]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Ecology.</emphasis>
Always found on bat guano, where it probably feeds on Diptera larvae (
<bibRefCitation author="Lackner, T. &amp; Pavicevic, D." pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="423 - 426" refId="ref74144" refString="Lackner, T. &amp; Pavicevic, D. (2008) Faunistic note on newly recorded and rare species of Histeridae from Serbia (Coleoptera). In: Pavicevic, D. &amp; Perreau, M. (Eds), Advances in the studies of the fauna of the Balkan Peninsula. Papers dedicated to the memory of Guido Nonveiller. Institute for Nature Conservation of Serbia, Belgrade, Monograph 22, pp. 423 - 426." type="journal article" year="2008">Lackner &amp; Pavićević 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,294,2017]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,273,820,846]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Notes.</emphasis>
In 
<bibRefCitation author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[313,607,821,847]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="173 - 175" refId="ref75329" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2005) Insecta Coleoptera Histeridae. In: Ruffo, S. &amp; Stoch, F. (Eds), Checklist e distribuzione della fauna italiana. Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2. serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita, 16, pp. 173 - 175, with data on CD-ROM." type="journal article" year="2005">Penati and Vienna (2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[619,692,821,847]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="173 - 175" refId="ref75399" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2006 a) Insecta Coleoptera Histeridae. In: Ruffo, S. &amp; Stoch, F. (Eds), Checklist and distribution of the Italian fauna. Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2. serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita, 17, pp. 173 - 175, with data on CD-ROM." type="journal article" year="2006">2006a</bibRefCitation>
) the date of capture of the specimens preserved in the Lostia di Santa 
<collectingRegion box="[222,284,858,884]" country="Bulgaria" name="Sofiya-Grad" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Sofia</collectingRegion>
collection (CUL) is erroneously given as “1939” (see “Data collection”); in fact, the label does not include a collection date, but reads “Grotta dell’Inferno / Scala di Giocca / leg. Dodero”, which proves without a doubt that this is one of the numerous specimens collected in 
<date box="[985,1112,934,960]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" value="1902-04">April 1902</date>
by the well-known Genoan entomologist and which Lostia received as a gift.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,294,2017]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">
In the most recent faunistic works on the Italian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1808" box="[777,897,1010,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Histeridae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Audisio, P. A. &amp; De Biase, A. &amp; Ferro, G. &amp; Mascagni, A. &amp; Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[914,1149,1010,1036]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 19" refId="ref72242" refString="Audisio, P. A., De Biase, A., Ferro, G., Mascagni, A., Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (1995) Coleoptera Myxophaga, Polyphaga I (Hydrophiloidea, Histeroidea). In: Minelli, A., Ruffo, S. &amp; La Posta, S. (Eds), Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana, 46. Calderini, Bologna, pp. 1 - 19." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Audisio 
<emphasis box="[1018,1071,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">et al</emphasis>
. 1995
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[1163,1431,1010,1036]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="75 - 83" refId="ref75260" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2002) Fascicolo 46 - Coleoptera Myxophaga, Polyphaga I (Hydrophiloidea, Histeroidea). In: Stoch, F. &amp; Zoia, S. (Eds), Aggiornamenti alla Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana. VII. Contributo. Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 134 (1), 75 - 83." type="journal article" year="2002">Penati &amp; Vienna 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[151,212,1047,1073]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="173 - 175" refId="ref75329" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2005) Insecta Coleoptera Histeridae. In: Ruffo, S. &amp; Stoch, F. (Eds), Checklist e distribuzione della fauna italiana. Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2. serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita, 16, pp. 173 - 175, with data on CD-ROM." type="journal article" year="2005">2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[224,298,1047,1073]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="173 - 175" refId="ref75399" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2006 a) Insecta Coleoptera Histeridae. In: Ruffo, S. &amp; Stoch, F. (Eds), Checklist and distribution of the Italian fauna. Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2. serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita, 17, pp. 173 - 175, with data on CD-ROM." type="journal article" year="2006">2006a</bibRefCitation>
) the record by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bertolani, R. &amp; Manicardi, G. C. &amp; Rebecchi, L." box="[474,733,1047,1073]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="61 - 77" refId="ref72542" refString="Bertolani, R., Manicardi, G. C. &amp; Rebecchi, L. (1994) Faunistic study in the karst complex of Frasassi (Genga, Italy). International Journal of Speleology, 23 (1 - 2), 61 - 77." type="journal article" year="1994">
Bertolani 
<emphasis box="[590,641,1048,1073]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">et al</emphasis>
. (1994)
</bibRefCitation>
was disregarded as a precaution. This was motivated by the fact that the specimens, although identified by one of the above authors (P. Vienna), could not be compared with the 
<typeStatus box="[261,311,1123,1149]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">type</typeStatus>
material and their identity was considered doubtful; additionally, until then the species had always been considered a Sardinian endemic and was known exclusively from Grotta dell’Inferno (
<emphasis box="[1316,1345,1161,1186]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">cf.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vienna, P." pageId="38" pageNumber="235" refId="ref76703" refString="Vienna, P. (1980) Fauna d'Italia XVI. Coleoptera Histeridae. Calderini, Bologna, 373 pp." type="book" year="1980">Vienna 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mazur, S." box="[226,372,1198,1224]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 379" refId="ref74808" refString="Mazur, S. (1984) A world catalogue of Histeridae. Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne, 54, 1 - 379." type="journal article" year="1984">Mazur 1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mazur, S." box="[386,448,1198,1224]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" refId="ref74831" refString="Mazur, S. (1997) A world catalogue of the Histeridae (Coleoptera: Histeroidea). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 377 pp." type="book" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
; etc.). Later, the finding of specimens in a cave near 
<collectingRegion box="[1081,1151,1198,1224]" country="Bulgaria" name="Vratsa" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Vraca</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1191,1292,1198,1224]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, H. &amp; Secq, M." pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="207 - 208" refId="ref76622" refString="Thomas, H. &amp; Secq, M. (2000) Gnathoncus cerberus Auzat, 1923: une espece nouvelle pour la faune Bulgare (Coleoptere Histeridae). Bulletin de la Societe Linneenne de Bordeaux, 28 (4), 207 - 208." type="journal article" year="2000">Thomas &amp; Secq 2000</bibRefCitation>
), but most of all the confirmation of the correct identification of the specimens from the 
<collectingRegion box="[1335,1436,1236,1262]" country="Italy" name="Marche" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Marches</collectingRegion>
after comparison with Sardinian ones and new catches, cleared all doubts about the presence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Auzat" authorityYear="1923" box="[1268,1407,1274,1300]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Gnathoncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerberus">
<emphasis box="[1268,1289,1274,1299]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1304,1407,1274,1299]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">cerberus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[268,324,1312,1338]" name="Italy" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Italy</collectingCountry>
, ignored also by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mazur, S." box="[526,688,1312,1338]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" refId="ref74858" refString="Mazur, S. (2004) Histeridae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Staphylinoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 68 - 102." type="book" year="2004">Mazur (2004)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Yelamos, T. &amp; Lackner, T." box="[747,1095,1312,1338]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" refId="ref77231" refString="Yelamos, T. &amp; Lackner, T. (2004) Fauna Europaea: Histeridae. In: Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. (Ed.), Fauna Europaea: Coleoptera 1. Fauna Europaea version 1.1, available at http: // www. faunaeur. org [accessed September 2009 as version 1.3 of April 19 th 2007.]" type="url" year="2004">Yélamos and Lackner (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. Lastly, the species was very recently recorded also from 
<collectingCountry box="[484,562,1349,1375]" name="Serbia" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">Serbia</collectingCountry>
, which suggests that “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="235">this species is spread over a much larger area, and that its apparent rarity owes to its secretive habits</emphasis>
” (
<bibRefCitation author="Lackner, T. &amp; Pavicevic, D." box="[768,1088,1387,1413]" pageId="38" pageNumber="235" pagination="423 - 426" refId="ref74144" refString="Lackner, T. &amp; Pavicevic, D. (2008) Faunistic note on newly recorded and rare species of Histeridae from Serbia (Coleoptera). In: Pavicevic, D. &amp; Perreau, M. (Eds), Advances in the studies of the fauna of the Balkan Peninsula. Papers dedicated to the memory of Guido Nonveiller. Institute for Nature Conservation of Serbia, Belgrade, Monograph 22, pp. 423 - 426." type="journal article" year="2008">Lackner &amp; Pavićević 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
